}}</ref>）位於[[喀麦隆|喀麦隆]]西部，距离首都[[雅温得|雅温得]]366公里，為[[西北省_(喀麦隆)|西北省]]的首府，是喀麦隆英語區的重要城市。

==歷史==
[[File:COLLECTIE_TROPENMUSEUM_Zicht_op_een_straat_en_de_huizen_van_Bamenda_TMnr_20014196.jpg|thumb]]
巴门达的歷史約起源於十八世紀，可能與{{le|巴姆穆王國|Kingdom of Bamum}}中[[提卡耳人|提卡耳人]]的聚落有關<ref> Toyin Falola, Daniel Jean-Jacques, ''Africa: An Encyclopedia of Culture and Society [3 volumes]: An Encyclopedia of Culture and Society'', ABC-CLIO, USA, 2015, p. 142</ref>。1884年，該地區為[[德國|德國]]佔領，1916年改由[[英國|英國]]與[[法國|法國]]管理<ref> Emmanuel Mbah, ''Environment and Identity Politics in Colonial Africa: Fulani Migrations and Land Conflict'', Taylor & Francis, UK, 2016, p. 20</ref>，1919年起由英國獨自管理。1961年，西北省加入前一年獨立的喀麥隆共和國<ref> Emmanuel Mbah, ''Environment and Identity Politics in Colonial Africa: Fulani Migrations and Land Conflict'', Taylor & Francis, UK, 2016, p. 21</ref>。

現時巴门达多數的居民均使用英語，英語衍生的[[喀麥隆皮欽語|喀麥隆皮欽語]]是當地街頭最常用的語言。1990年，喀麦隆最大的反對黨{{le|喀麦隆社会民主阵线|Social Democratic Front (Cameroon)}}於巴门达成立<ref name=Launch>[http://www.sdfparty.org/english/history/128.php "Significant Events in the Life of the Social Democratic Front"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070719120156/http://www.sdfparty.org/english/history/128.php |date=2007-07-19 }}, SDF website.</ref>。另外主張[[南喀麥隆|南喀麥隆]]（原屬[[英屬喀麥隆|英屬喀麥隆]]）獨立的[[南喀麦隆全国委员会|南喀麦隆全国委员会]]（SCNC）亦於1994年在巴门达成立<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bareta.news/bamenda-forgotten-city/|title=BAMENDA: A FORGOTTEN CITY AND THE PEOPLE CRY FOR GOOD ROADS|website=www.bareta.news|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-29|archive-date=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009100245/https://www.bareta.news/bamenda-forgotten-city/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==現況==
[[File:A_treet_in_Bamenda_Cameroon.jpg|thumb]]
巴门达主要的經濟產業為[[咖啡|咖啡]]等農產品的加工業、食物加工、手工藝、[[家庭代工|家庭代工]]、教育與旅遊業等<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Britannica|url=https://www.britannica.com/place/Bamenda|title=Bamenda|access-date=2019-10-09|archive-date=2020-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101082910/https://www.britannica.com/place/Bamenda|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

交通方面，巴门达有道路連接首都雅温得與第一大城[[杜阿拉|杜阿拉]]，北側為[[巴門達高原|巴門達高原]]，有一長367公里的[[環路|環狀公路]]<ref> Mark Dike DeLancey, Mark W. Delancey, Rebecca Neh Mbuh, ''Historical Dictionary of the Republic of Cameroon'', Rowman & Littlefield, USA, 2019, p. 57</ref>。另外市內有[[巴門達機場|巴門達機場]]（{{airport codes|BPC|FKKV}}）<ref name=WAD>{{WAD|FKKV|source=[[DAFIF|DAFIF]]}}</ref>，有[[喀麥隆航空_(2006年)|喀麥隆航空]]航班起降<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cameroon-info.net/article/cameroun-aviation-civile-camair-co-reussit-son-vol-test-vers-bamenda-293202.html|title=Cameroon-Info.Net :: Cameroun-Info.Net: Le Portail du Cameroun|website=www.cameroon-info.net|language=fr|access-date=2017-07-05|archive-date=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009100246/http://www.cameroon-info.net/article/cameroun-aviation-civile-camair-co-reussit-son-vol-test-vers-bamenda-293202.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

教育方面，[[巴門達大學|巴門達大學]]於2010年成立，為喀麥隆第二所以英語授課的大學（第一所為[[布埃亞大學|布埃亞大學]]）<ref>{{cite web | url =https://www.cameroonweb.com/CameroonHomePage/education/ | title =Education in Cameroon | publisher =CameroonWeb | access-date =11 September 2018 | quote =Originally The University of Buea was the only Anglo-Saxon style university, but with the University of Bamenda opening its doors in 2011 Cameroon now has two English Universities. | archive-date =2020-08-05 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20200805172012/https://www.cameroonweb.com/CameroonHomePage/education/ | dead-url =no }}</ref>。

==氣候==
巴门达屬[[熱帶莽原氣候|熱帶莽原氣候]]，夏季有較長的雨季，冬季則為乾季。

[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]指巴门达是非洲[[細懸浮微粒|細懸浮微粒]]（PM2.5）污染最嚴重的城市之一<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jayshree|first1=Nandi|title=Delhi no more the most polluted city in the world, says WHO report|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/Delhi-no-more-the-most-polluted-city-in-the-world-says-WHO-report/articleshow/52232427.cms|accessdate=12 May 2016|work=[[Times_of_India|Times of India]]|date=12 May 2016|archive-date=2019-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507081135/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/Delhi-no-more-the-most-polluted-city-in-the-world-says-WHO-report/articleshow/52232427.cms|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
